If everyone contributes all their coins to the public fund, the total amount will be maximized and each player will receive a high return due to the multiplication by 2.8.

However, there is also the risk that others might not contribute, hoping to enjoy the benefits without sacrificing their own coins—a strategy known as free-riding. This could lead to a lower overall public fund and consequently lower payoffs for everyone.

My strategy will involve starting with a cooperative approach by contributing all my coins to the public fund. This could set a positive precedent and foster trust among group members.
